<h2>◆ Projects ◆</h2>
<p>Things I've built, maintained, or contributed to.</p>

<h3><a href="https://github.com/janus-llm">Janus LLM</a></h3>
<p>
  A library for IT modernization using large language models, RAG, and
  intelligent code chunking. Built for government sponsors at MITRE.
</p>

<h3><a href="https://github.com/mitrefireline/simfire">SimFire</a></h3>
<p>
  A wildfire simulator written in Python, designed for reinforcement learning
  research. Used alongside SimHarness for wildfire mitigation experiments.
  Published at NeurIPS 2023.
</p>

<h3><a href="https://github.com/mitrefireline/simharness">SimHarness</a></h3>
<p>
  The RL training harness that pairs with SimFire. Handles agent training,
  reward shaping, and experiment management for wildfire mitigation research.
</p>

<h3><a href="https://github.com/doyled-it/complicit.work">complicit.work</a></h3>
<p>
  A moral culpability calculator for occupations. Enter your job title and
  employer, get a transparent ethical evaluation with a numerical score,
  reasoning for every variable, a "Moral Price Tag" showing the dollar value
  of your ethical compromise, and real job market alternatives. Built with
  Next.js, Tailwind, and the Anthropic API.
</p>

<h3><a href="https://github.com/doyled-it/agent-view">agent-view</a></h3>
<p>
  An OpenTUI-based terminal interface for managing and monitoring AI coding
  agent sessions. Forked and improved from the original, currently being
  ported to Rust.
</p>

<h3><a href="https://github.com/doyled-it/claude-vault-skills">claude-vault-skills</a></h3>
<p>
  A Claude Code skill suite for managing an Obsidian vault as a productivity
